Citation.sTitle: Vapor - liquid equilibria of fluoroethane (HFC-161) + 2,3,3,3 - tetrafluoroprop - 1 - ene (HFO- 1234yf)
Citation.sAbstract: In this study, isothermal vapor liquid equilibrium (VLE) data were measured for the binary system of fluoroethane (HFC-161) + 2,3,3,3-tetrafluoroprop-1-ene (HFO-1234yf) over the whole composition range in the temperature range from 283.15 to 323.15 K at 10 K intervals. The experimental VLE data were correlated with the Peng Robinson equation of state. The van derWaals (vdW) one-fluid mixing rule and the Wong-Sandler (WS) mixing rule with the non-random two-liquid (NRTL) activity coefficient model were both used. The correlation results show good agreement with the experimental data.
